</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
An additional relatively large 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Diaphus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diaphus" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Diaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of about 6.0 mm in length is observed in the Ichishi Group and will be described separately by one of us (YT). It also belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brauer" baseAuthorityYear="1904" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Diaphus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diaphus splendidus" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="splendidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Diaphus splendidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
otolith group and is characterized by a relatively long and sharp rostrum, a high postdorsal angle, and the lack of a postdorsal concavity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gilbert" authorityYear="1906" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Diaphus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diaphus garmani" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="garmani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Diaphus garmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Otolith Group after 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwarzhans, W" journalOrPublisher="Palaeo Ichthyologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="41 - 82" refId="B58" refString="Schwarzhans, W, 2013a. A comparative morphological study of the Recent otoliths of the genera Diaphus, Idiolychnus and Lobianchia (Myctophidae). Palaeo Ichthyologica 13: 41 - 82" title="A comparative morphological study of the Recent otoliths of the genera Diaphus, Idiolychnus and Lobianchia (Myctophidae)." volume="13" year="2013 a">Schwarzhans (2013a)</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
